Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water
to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%g}.

Put the @Crumbled Blue Cheese{30%g} and the @Breadcrumbs{25%g} in a #bowl{} and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in the @Olive Oil{2%tbsp} for the crumb, then set your
blue cheese crumb aside for later.

Halve any large @Cauliflower Florets{300%g} and pop them into an #ovenproof dish{}. Drizzle
with oil and season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden brown and tender,
~{15-20%mins}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, stir in the @Macaroni{180%g} and bring back
to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with oil and
stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, melt the @Butter{20%g} in a saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once the butter has melted, add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%g}. Stir-fry
until golden, ~{4-5%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook it thoroughly.

Next, stir in the @Plain Flour{2%tbsp}. Cook, stirring, until it forms a paste,
~{1-2%mins} - you've made a roux!

Gradually stir in the @Water for the Sauce{250%ml} and the @Vegetable Stock Paste{15%g}.
Bring to the boil, stir and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%mins}.

Stir in the @Creme Fraiche{150%g}, then remove from the heat.

Add the grated cheese to the sauce and stir until melted.

Next, stir the roasted cauli and cooked pasta through the bacon sauce, then pour back
into the ovenproof dish.

Turn your grill on to high.

Sprinkle the blue cheese crumb evenly over the top, then grill the mac and cheese on
the top shelf of your oven until the crumb is golden, ~{3-5%mins}.

Serve your bacon mac and cheese in #bowls{} with the @Sriracha Sauce{15%g} drizzled
over the top.

> Add less sriracha if you'd prefer things milder. Enjoy!